        <headline>Flood Advisory issued July 27 at 6:22PM CDT until July 27 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by earlier excessive rainfall continues,
although the threat for additional heavy rain has ended.

* WHERE...A portion of northeast Illinois, including the following
counties, Cook and DuPage.

* WHEN...Until 800 PM CDT.

* IMPACTS...Standing water continues to impact numerous roads across
the advisory area. Some creeks may continue to rise out of their
banks.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 618 PM CDT, Doppler radar and automated rain gauges
indicated that between 1 and 3 inches of rain fell with
earlier heavy thunderstorms.
- Some locations that will continue to experience flooding
include...
Addison, Elmhurst, Melrose Park, Bellwood, Westchester, Oak
Brook, Villa Park, Clarendon Hills.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>A Flood Advisory means minor flooding along waterways and other poor
drainage areas is imminent or may already be occurring. Persons in
the advisory area should use caution and avoid flood waters.</instruction>
